@startuml
title FIG-19-01. Choosing the Right Data Architecture View
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml
top to bottom direction
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 90
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 12
}

rectangle "Start with the data question" as START #E8F1F8

rectangle "1. Which business information\nconcepts matter?" as Q1
rectangle "2. What precise, technology-independent\nstructure is required?" as Q2
rectangle "3. How will the data be stored\nin a chosen technology?" as Q3
rectangle "4. Where does data move,\ntransform and rest?" as Q4
rectangle "5. Where did a value originate, how was\nit transformed and where is it used?" as Q5
rectangle "6. Who is accountable and\nwho performs stewardship?" as Q6
rectangle "7. What happens from creation\nthrough retention and disposal?" as Q7
rectangle "8. Which shared subjects, classifications\nor controlled values are governed?" as Q8
rectangle "Clarify the data boundary\nand architecture decision" as CLARIFY #FFF8DC

rectangle "Conceptual\ninformation view" as V1 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Logical ERD" as V2 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Physical\ndata model" as V3 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Data flow\ndiagram (DFD)" as V4 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Data lineage\nview" as V5 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Ownership\nmatrix" as V6 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Data lifecycle\nview" as V7 #EAF4EA
rectangle "Master/reference\ndata catalogue" as V8 #EAF4EA

START -down-> Q1 : begin
Q1 -right-> V1 : yes
Q1 -down-> Q2 : no
Q2 -right-> V2 : yes
Q2 -down-> Q3 : no
Q3 -right-> V3 : yes
Q3 -down-> Q4 : no
Q4 -right-> V4 : yes
Q4 -down-> Q5 : no
Q5 -right-> V5 : yes
Q5 -down-> Q6 : no
Q6 -right-> V6 : yes
Q6 -down-> Q7 : no
Q7 -right-> V7 : yes
Q7 -down-> Q8 : no
Q8 -right-> V8 : yes
Q8 -down-> CLARIFY : no

note left of START
Before drawing:
state audience, boundary
and abstraction level.

More than one concern?
Use separate linked views
with stable names and identifiers.
end note

' Accessibility notes:
' - Arrowheads show direction from start, through each question, to its first view.
' - Yes/no labels make each branch explicit without relying on colour.
' - Question numbers and text labels carry the complete meaning.
' - Orthogonal connectors and aligned rows avoid crossings.
' - The figure is a first filter, not a substitute for the chapter table.
@enduml
